The Republic of Finland filed withthe Securities and Exchange Commission for a shelf offering ofup to 550 mln dlrs of debt securities, including notes andbonds, and/or warrants to buy debt securities on terms to bedetermined at the time of the sale.    The offering is in addition to 50 mln dlrs of debtsecurities already registered with the SEC but unsold.    Proceeds from the sale will be used to finance capitalinvestment and the promotion of productive investments andexports designed to strengthen the country's balance ofpayments, the government said. No underwriter was named. Reuter&#3;